data.col_1: For last mile delivery, truck with cargo values more than USD 100,000, ASUS require at the least two professional armed escorts, one is in front of truck for guiding delivery route and the other is following truck to monitor. all excorts should be with proactive GPS monitoring and prompt response for recoverying process,lke panic button, GPS abnormal auto alert and so on and if truck with cargo values more than USD 600,000, it should spilt to another truck. (USD 600,000 for one truck is limitation)
For AIR, escort is required for protecting ASUS cargos from terminal to airport warehouse.
For last mile delivery of CY-CFS/Air, only BOX trailer allowed.

The trailer must be equipped with GPS tracking technology. The GPS system should be actively monitored during the transit. In addition, protocols must be in place should an alarm be activated, which alerts a dedicated security company (and/or police) who can attempt to recover the shipment.

Your local agent to this contract may use its own vehicles or can subcontract to another trucking company, however, your local agent is only allowed to subcontract one-tier down. To be clear this means that the subcontracted trucker cannot themselves subcontract out. All subcontractors should be clearly listed while you submit RFQ to ASUS. ASUS must be informed in case of any new subcontractor used during RFQ contract period.
A written contract, security requirements and operation procedure with trucking company must be in place.
Driver has to be reach able by mobile phone during transportation

During transportation or in the case that driver needs to be temporarily away from truck in any cirsumstance, the container/trailer must be sealed and locked with a locking mechanism which prevents either left or right door of trailer being opened. Samples of locks are shown in appendix.
The driver has to check if the trailer or container's  seal or lock is damage after every stop or rest period.

It is not allowed to leave the truck unless official secured packing lot is used, which has:
    - CCTV
    - Guard
    - Dedicated security barrier
    - Perimeter fencing
    - Sufficient lighting
If it is necessary to refuel then it should be planned at a filling station with adequate security, CCTV and driver should never leave keys inside vehicle.

In the event of delay as a consequence of mechanical problems, breakdown of the vehicle, accidents, traffic jams, road diversions and the like, the driver is obliged to inform the operations center and not to leave the vehicle. If the driver is injured and sent to hospital, your representative must be there to secure ASUS cargos until the following steps are well arranged under good security management.
For local delivery, parking outside a secure parking lot (as defined) is not allowed. Where a slot time is missed or cancelled, cargo should be returned to the secured warehouse / packing lot.

When picking-up container from a terminal, please carefully check if seal is missing or broken. In case of any seal abnormality (missing or broken), please take pictures, inform ASUS immeidately of seal status with photos, and also add another security lock to protect a container. The following steps will be adivsed by ASUS.
For CY direct delivery from Durban, if it's too late to deliver to customer warehouse within the same day, the container needs to park in a secured warehouse and deliver the next day.
Delivery route to customer warehouse should be fixed and offered in advance. The Rule should be stricted followed that main route only and side route prohibited.

For CY delivery, 2 clamps should be applied and trackable during transit. 
For Air/CY-CFS delivery, an extra lock should be used to prevent either left or right door of trailer from being opened. Samples of locks are shown in appendix.
